cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with spectrum management in cognitive radio networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper formulates the problem as a non-cooperative game, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves optimization of resource allocation, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for access point selection and power allocation, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves simulations to evaluate the proposed algorithms, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves processing and analysis of data.
